 font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">ie</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">, Invest NI &amp;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> its various predecessors – with the result that bank finance traditionally played a lesser </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">role in NI than in GB.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Have NI</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> banks continued to play a lesser role in commercial finance than elsewhere – in particular, have economic and financial conditions s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">ince 2008 exacerbated that position? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 9pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">2.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Santander</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">’s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> ambition to be the bank of choice for companies across the country</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, including</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Northern Ireland</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 9pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">2.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">While some of the banks</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> operating</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Northern Ireland</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> have seen a declining appetite for lending si</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">nce 2008, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Santander</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is committed to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> grow</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ing this part of its business in the years ahead. O</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ur experience over the last 18 months</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> suggests that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> there is no shortage of SMEs seeking funding in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Northern Ireland</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">2.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In 2012, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Santander</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> grew its net lending to SMEs in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Northern Ireland</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> by 27%.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> This compares to a national lending increase by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Santander</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> of 18%. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Our commitment to grow our lending to SMEs in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Northern Ireland</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> has continued into 2013. As of 30 June 2013, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Santander</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> grew its ne</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">t lending to SMEs </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Northern Ireland</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">by 32% from a year earlier. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">2.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Funding for expansion for companies in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Northern Ireland</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, as in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Great Britain</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, is often provided by banks in the form of invoice finance or factoring. These provide a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">high </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">level of control and transparency, especially for younger businesses. These products are likely to remain popular for banks and businesses in the years ahead.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">2.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Providing banking products for start up businesses is a challenge that banks face in both </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Gre</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">at Britain</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Northern Ireland</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. Banks find it difficult to provide lending to new businesses due to a lack of track record and, usually, a lack of trading data on which to base risk assessments. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">2.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">UK </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Government has sought to overcome this problem thro</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ugh the Start-Up Loans programme. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Santander</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> supports this initiative and considers it an excellent</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> example of how g</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">overnment can help more start up businesses grow and create jobs. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">2.7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Start-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Up Loans are available to business in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Northern Ireland</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:12.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Lack of e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ffectiveness of national initiatives to help aid economic recovery</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Is the population of NI at a disadvantage to the rest of the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">UK</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> as a result of the lack of uptake of national economic recovery initiatives by banks in NI?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">3.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Santander</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> participates in a number</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> of g</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">overnment schemes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> available in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Northern Ireland</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> designed to help </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">boost</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the economic</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> recovery. Thes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e include: </span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Funding for Lending Scheme</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.06pt;