 that the British Bankers Association </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">(BBA) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">has agreed to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">lead an industry initiative to increase the amount of publicly available data on bank lending in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Northern Ireland</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Sant</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ander</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> refers the Committee to the BBA’s response for more detail on this matter.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">How is new lending recorded; how much ‘new’ lending recorded is actually made up of extensions or additions to existing loans; and what </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">are banks actually doing compared t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">o what they are advertising? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">4.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Santander</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> has only been operating as a corporate bank in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Northern Ireland</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> for the last 3 years. As most of our loan facilities last for a 5 year period, we have not yet had any </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">customer facilities expire which need</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> renewing. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Consequently, the vast majority of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">our </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">lending recorded in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Northern Ireland</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> is new lending. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:12.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Access to banking in rural communities</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Following the closure of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Danske</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> Bank of some branches in rural areas, are the interests of those living in more rural areas, particularly the elderly, sufficiently fulfilled by the banking structure as it currently stands? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 9pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 2